18 fev 9h00: Palais Impérial 

>> From Haneda Airport
Take the Keihin Express train from Haneda Airport Station, all the way to Shinagawa. At Shinagawa, change to the Yamanote Line and get off at Shibuya Station. It takes around 40-60 minutes, costs around 600 yen, and there are trains every few minutes. There are buses from the airport too, which you can reserve on the day, and which are good if you have a lot of luggage.

>> How to get to us from Shibuya Station
① Find Shibuya Station Exit 8 exit for "Hachiko" which is a famous statue of a dog and local landmark. When you exit near Hachiko, you will find yourself in a big square next to the famous Scramble Crossing.
② Go across the crossing, and walk down Inokashira Street - when looking across from the Scramble Crossing, it's the street with the TSUTAYA store on your left, and the MAGNET department store on your right.
③ Keep going straight down this road for 300m. You will pass a big department store called MODI around halfway so you know you are on the correct street. Keep going straight past MODI.
④ When you reach a crossroads with a big yellow TOWER RECORDS building, take a left (up a little hill).
⑤ Keep walking 100m, and you will find a furniture shop ACME FURNITURE on your left. The entrance to The Millennials Shibuya is hidden away just before the furniture shop. Please take the elevator up to the 4th floor to check in!


